WEBVTT

00:00.500 --> 00:02.235
Male announcer:
Previously, on Life...

00:02.338 --> 00:03.473
Detective, I have something

00:03.506 --> 00:05.075
you might be interested in.

00:05.108 --> 00:06.742
The Bank of Los Angeles
shootout.

00:06.776 --> 00:07.743
Crews:
That was 15 years ago.

00:07.777 --> 00:09.079
You should ask your partner

00:09.112 --> 00:11.147
what happened to all that money.

00:11.181 --> 00:12.348
Bobby said--

00:12.382 --> 00:13.425
I don't know what
your old partner told you,

00:13.449 --> 00:15.418
but he was working
the barricades four blocks out.

00:15.451 --> 00:16.452
Hi.

00:16.486 --> 00:17.620
Hello.

00:17.653 --> 00:18.721
I'm Olivia.

00:18.754 --> 00:20.556
Ted:
The thing about Olivia is

00:20.590 --> 00:23.526
she's marrying your father.

00:30.833 --> 00:33.603
I wanna tell you about
the dream I had last night.

00:33.636 --> 00:35.438
Were there clowns in it?

00:35.471 --> 00:36.572
No.

00:36.606 --> 00:38.974
I don't like dreams with clowns.

00:39.008 --> 00:39.842
Who does?

00:39.875 --> 00:42.011
No, there were no clowns
in this dream.

00:42.044 --> 00:44.046
There were solar panels.

00:44.079 --> 00:46.081
An array of solar panels.

00:46.115 --> 00:47.116
Solar panels?

00:47.149 --> 00:48.884
I wanna buy a solar farm.

00:48.918 --> 00:50.420
You already have
an orange grove.

00:50.453 --> 00:52.388
And now I want a solar farm.

00:52.422 --> 00:55.024
Energy, Ted, made out of light.

00:55.057 --> 00:59.094
Solar farms don't exactly
turn in a huge profit, Charlie.

00:59.128 --> 01:02.832
The profit will be
in our small contribution

01:02.865 --> 01:04.900
to restoring the natural
harmony of our planet.

01:04.934 --> 01:07.470
I don't think there's a column
in the spreadsheet

01:07.503 --> 01:10.139
under restoration
of planetary harmony.

01:10.172 --> 01:12.141
I want that solar farm, Ted.

01:12.174 --> 01:14.477
It came to me in a dream.

01:17.647 --> 01:20.616
[Upbeat rock music]

01:20.650 --> 01:27.990
♫

01:36.532 --> 01:38.701
In the back by the sody pop.

01:43.573 --> 01:46.041
You're not gonna like it though.

02:09.799 --> 02:10.900
No IDs.

02:10.933 --> 02:13.469
They look like
Persian kids though.

02:15.638 --> 02:18.207
Wrote it in oil.

02:19.975 --> 02:21.977
Hate crime?
Skinheads?

02:22.011 --> 02:23.746
Cash in the register
went untouched.

02:23.779 --> 02:26.015
Nothing stolen.
Just those two there.

02:26.048 --> 02:28.083
Crews:
Two dead
Iranian-Americans in here.

02:28.117 --> 02:29.985
Bunch of angry people out there.

02:30.019 --> 02:32.254
Get some more units down here.

02:32.287 --> 02:34.223
There were three of 'em.

02:34.456 --> 02:36.726
Early 20s maybe, you know.

02:36.759 --> 02:38.928
They were wearing ski masks.

02:38.961 --> 02:40.395
And they each had a gun.

02:40.429 --> 02:41.330
What happened then?

02:41.363 --> 02:42.832
They were over by the cooler

02:42.865 --> 02:44.233
makin' a lot of noise.

02:44.266 --> 02:46.969
One of 'em was saying, "Go back
to where you came from."

02:47.002 --> 02:51.206
The other one kept saying,
"This is where I came from."

02:51.240 --> 02:53.976
Then I heard two shots,
and then it was quiet.

02:54.009 --> 02:57.246
[Crowd commotion]

02:57.279 --> 02:59.248
[Bang bang bang]

03:08.290 --> 03:10.325
Whoa. Hold it, hold it.

03:14.029 --> 03:15.397
Firecrackers. M80s.

03:15.430 --> 03:16.799
No gun.

03:16.832 --> 03:18.367
Just firecrackers.
No gun.

03:20.269 --> 03:21.937
That's all this crowd needs.

03:21.971 --> 03:23.005
You got this?

03:23.038 --> 03:24.139
Yeah.

03:24.173 --> 03:25.474
Man: Hey!

03:25.507 --> 03:28.177
You threw those!

03:29.244 --> 03:32.748
[All shouting]

03:51.166 --> 03:53.302
More units?

03:53.335 --> 03:55.404
More units.

03:57.873 --> 04:01.210
[Woman speaking in Farsi]

04:01.243 --> 04:03.412
Shahnaz:
You're not listening
to us.

04:03.445 --> 04:05.247
Officer:
No, you're not
listening to me.

04:05.280 --> 04:07.092
I'll ask you one more time
to step out of the store.

04:07.116 --> 04:08.984
It's okay.
I got this, officer.

04:09.018 --> 04:11.120
[Speaking Farsi]
All yours, detective.

04:13.255 --> 04:15.057
Why is she so upset?

04:15.090 --> 04:16.091
Amir, my brother,

04:16.125 --> 04:18.127
he was stopping here
on the way home from class.

04:18.160 --> 04:20.195
And he never came home?

04:20.229 --> 04:23.232
[Speaking Farsi]

04:30.339 --> 04:31.841
[Gasps]

04:32.942 --> 04:33.976
Is he your brother Amir?

04:34.009 --> 04:36.378
No. But those are his friends,
Rashne and Daria.

04:36.411 --> 04:39.014
[Roya speaking Farsi]

04:39.048 --> 04:40.049
What's she saying?

04:40.082 --> 04:42.117
Amir came to this store
with Rashne and Daria.

04:42.151 --> 04:44.053
But if he's not here,
he must have been taken.

04:44.086 --> 04:45.086
They must have taken him.

04:45.087 --> 04:46.088
Who?

04:46.121 --> 04:47.561
Whoever did this
to Rashne and Daria.

04:49.224 --> 04:57.199
♫

05:03.272 --> 05:05.540
"Go home."

05:05.574 --> 05:08.277
I bet those kids
thought they were home.

05:17.486 --> 05:19.087
Hey, nice job out there, Bobby.

05:19.120 --> 05:20.889
That knucklehead
with the tire iron?

05:20.922 --> 05:22.023
Yeah, it's nothin'.

05:22.056 --> 05:24.726
Hey, it was only nothing
'cause you did something to him.

05:24.759 --> 05:26.495
If you hadn't done anything,

05:26.528 --> 05:27.838
it might have become
any number of things.

05:27.862 --> 05:29.398
Do you have to wind him up?

05:29.431 --> 05:30.665
Any number of things.

05:30.699 --> 05:31.709
That guy with the tire iron

05:31.733 --> 05:34.035
hits the other guy,
and the whole place goes up.

05:34.068 --> 05:35.570
A butterfly flaps its wings,

05:35.604 --> 05:37.406
and halfway across the world,

05:37.439 --> 05:38.773
a hurricane forms.

05:38.807 --> 05:39.741
See? No matter
where it starts,

05:39.774 --> 05:41.710
always ends up with
something just like that.

05:41.743 --> 05:43.745
Something, nothing, anything.

05:43.778 --> 05:44.846
A butterfly, a hurricane.

05:44.879 --> 05:46.748
It'll make a good story.

05:46.781 --> 05:49.851
It's no Bank of Los Angeles,

05:49.884 --> 05:51.886
but at least it's true, right?

05:51.920 --> 05:52.754
What'd you say?

05:52.787 --> 05:54.789
Nothing.

05:54.823 --> 05:57.426
No. You said
something.

05:57.459 --> 05:59.861
See? Something? Nothing.
Can't get away from it.

06:00.644 --> 06:01.479
You mention the butterfly,

06:01.512 --> 06:03.414
I'm gonna find it
and rip its wings off.

06:03.447 --> 06:05.849
What did you say about
the Bank of Los Angeles?

06:05.883 --> 06:08.486
It's just a story
I like to tell, detective.

06:08.519 --> 06:09.587
Why? What's it to you?

06:09.620 --> 06:10.621
What kinda story?

06:10.654 --> 06:12.523
You're stepping over
a line here.

06:12.556 --> 06:14.625
You might wanna step back.

06:23.601 --> 06:26.904
[Background conversation]

06:26.937 --> 06:28.239
Full house.

06:28.272 --> 06:30.341
Reese: Yeah, I count FBI,

06:30.374 --> 06:32.610
Homeland Security,
Mayor's Office.

06:32.643 --> 06:33.744
Joint Terrorism Task Force,

06:33.777 --> 06:36.214
Hate Crimes Unit.

06:37.681 --> 06:41.285
Davis:
This is still a homicide,
first and foremost.

06:41.319 --> 06:42.653
And unless
the federal government

06:42.686 --> 06:45.623
is requesting the LAPD
relinquish its jurisdiction,

06:45.656 --> 06:47.625
it will be handled as a homicide

06:47.658 --> 06:50.261
and run by LAPD
homicide detectives.

06:56.500 --> 06:58.336
Reese: Rashne Talebi

06:58.369 --> 06:59.303
and Daria Ovesi.

06:59.337 --> 07:02.340
Each shot once in the head
at close range.

07:02.373 --> 07:03.883
Both are third year
at USC Business School.

07:03.907 --> 07:04.942
Both honor students.

07:04.975 --> 07:07.345
Both had juvie beefs
for dealing pot.

07:07.378 --> 07:08.612
Records were expunged.

07:08.646 --> 07:09.913
Crews:
Three white males

07:09.947 --> 07:11.515
wearing ski masks

07:11.549 --> 07:13.384
left the white
counter guy alone.

07:13.417 --> 07:15.386
Put the dead victims
in the cooler.

07:15.419 --> 07:18.589
Wrote "go home" in motor oil
on the cooler door.

07:18.622 --> 07:20.658
Amir Darvashi,
classmate of the victims.

07:20.691 --> 07:22.760
He was reported to be
at the gas station

07:22.793 --> 07:24.462
at the time of the shooting.

07:24.495 --> 07:25.363
Hasn't been seen since.

07:25.396 --> 07:27.731
Witnesses on scene
said they saw a van

07:27.765 --> 07:29.733
leaving the parking lot
at high speed

07:29.767 --> 07:31.269
just after the shooting.

07:31.302 --> 07:32.736
Color of this van could be blue,

07:32.770 --> 07:34.805
light gray, or beige.

07:34.838 --> 07:36.907
Pull over every vehicle
that even looks close.

07:36.940 --> 07:38.809
This neighborhood
was predominately white

07:38.842 --> 07:41.512
but has had a heavy Persian
influx since the '80s.

07:41.545 --> 07:42.980
Now it's about evenly split.

07:43.013 --> 07:45.015
This needs to close
and close fast.

07:45.048 --> 07:47.585
I do not need the war here.

07:51.655 --> 07:54.358
I've arranged to meet
the owner of the gas station--

07:54.392 --> 07:55.793
Mary Ann Farmer.

07:55.826 --> 07:57.328
And you?

07:57.361 --> 07:58.505
Mother of the missing boy Amir.

07:58.529 --> 08:00.364
I'll see what I can find out

08:00.398 --> 08:01.599
about him and his friends.

08:04.368 --> 08:05.603
[Line rings]

08:05.636 --> 08:06.504
Ted:
Charlie?

08:06.537 --> 08:09.607
I have one word for you--
photodiode.

08:09.640 --> 08:11.041
I don't know what that means.

08:11.074 --> 08:13.411
It means
transduced light energy.

08:13.444 --> 08:15.279
Energy from light, Charlie.

08:15.313 --> 08:17.047
From the sun.

08:17.080 --> 08:19.016
We can do this?

08:19.049 --> 08:21.051
I know what I said
at breakfast this morning.

08:21.084 --> 08:23.387
But I've been thinking
about what you said,

08:23.421 --> 08:24.555
about your dream.

08:24.588 --> 08:26.557
You're right, Charlie.
We are choking.

08:26.590 --> 08:28.492
Choking on fossil fuel.

08:28.526 --> 08:29.860
You found an array?

08:29.893 --> 08:31.662
Yeah. I'm on my way
right now to see it.

08:31.695 --> 08:33.664
Oh, uh, Ted, Olivia.

08:35.333 --> 08:36.634
Olivia?

08:36.667 --> 08:37.844
I told her to come by the house.

08:37.868 --> 08:39.837
You know, so we could--
we could talk.

08:39.870 --> 08:41.639
You didn't tell me that.

08:41.672 --> 08:43.541
No. There's things
I don't tell you, Ted.

08:43.574 --> 08:46.544
But... Olivia...

08:46.577 --> 08:47.778
She's coming by the house.

08:47.811 --> 08:49.513
Just explain to her
something came up

08:49.547 --> 08:50.814
and I can't get away, okay?

08:50.848 --> 08:52.616
Thanks.

08:54.652 --> 08:57.555
I was gonna see the solar farm.

08:57.588 --> 09:00.658
Maybe she'd like to go with me.

09:00.691 --> 09:02.593
Yeah, right.

09:02.626 --> 09:06.764
Because women really like
photovoltaic arrays.

09:06.797 --> 09:08.766
[Doorbell rings]

09:28.486 --> 09:29.920
Detective Crews?

09:29.953 --> 09:31.789
Ms. Farmer?

09:31.822 --> 09:32.923
Mary Ann.

09:32.956 --> 09:34.625
You look surprised.

09:36.527 --> 09:38.796
No, no.
No, I, um...

09:40.063 --> 09:41.932
No, I guess I just
expected, um--

09:41.965 --> 09:43.567
someone older.

09:43.601 --> 09:45.803
Maybe.

09:45.836 --> 09:47.476
Careful of having
expectations, detective.

09:47.505 --> 09:49.640
They only lead
to disappointment.

09:49.673 --> 09:50.553
Where'd you hear that?

09:50.574 --> 09:51.909
That one I didn't hear.

09:51.942 --> 09:54.912
That one I had to learn.

09:54.945 --> 09:56.547
Is it okay to go inside?

09:56.580 --> 09:57.981
I'm not gonna
disturb the evidence?

09:58.015 --> 09:59.617
No, it's okay.

10:01.619 --> 10:02.920
This is my first store.

10:02.953 --> 10:04.988
Your first?
How many do you have?

10:05.022 --> 10:06.156
Six.

10:06.189 --> 10:07.725
But this is my first.

10:09.560 --> 10:10.494
[Speaking Farsi]

10:10.528 --> 10:12.029
He's a good student.

10:12.062 --> 10:13.731
His friends are good students.

10:13.764 --> 10:16.600
His friends aren't such
good students, Mrs. Darvashi.

10:16.634 --> 10:18.636
They've both been arrested
for selling drugs.

10:18.669 --> 10:20.471
[Speaking Farsi]

10:20.504 --> 10:21.905
But not my Amir.

10:21.939 --> 10:23.040
No. Not your Amir.

10:23.073 --> 10:25.443
Those two,
the ones who were killed.

10:26.977 --> 10:28.679
He's not like them.

10:33.651 --> 10:34.985
Look at what a good student

10:35.018 --> 10:36.153
my Amir is--all A's.

10:36.186 --> 10:39.690
[Roya speaking Farsi]

10:41.559 --> 10:43.661
He would have called
his mother if he could.

10:43.694 --> 10:45.395
Someone is stopping him.

10:47.865 --> 10:49.967
You find him.

10:50.000 --> 10:52.035
You find my Amir.

11:05.883 --> 11:08.018
To die that way.

11:08.051 --> 11:11.622
To do that to another person,
that's so... terrible.

11:13.657 --> 11:14.992
"Go home."

11:15.025 --> 11:16.994
I was wondering

11:17.027 --> 11:19.229
if you might know
why they wrote that.

11:19.262 --> 11:21.031
I suppose out of hate.

11:21.064 --> 11:22.165
But it's in your store,

11:22.199 --> 11:24.635
and that made me think,
why here?

11:24.668 --> 11:26.504
Could it have something
to do with this place,

11:26.537 --> 11:27.671
with your store?

11:27.705 --> 11:30.508
Mary Ann, we have
surveillance tape

11:30.541 --> 11:32.610
from your camera
before it was destroyed.

11:32.643 --> 11:34.545
I'd like you to have
a look at it.

11:34.578 --> 11:36.680
Of course. Should I come
down to the station?

11:36.714 --> 11:40.518
No.
Actually, I have it here.

11:40.551 --> 11:42.620
What-- in that?

11:43.554 --> 11:45.756
Wow, that's like...

11:45.789 --> 11:48.025
Living in the future?

11:48.058 --> 11:49.560
Exactly.

11:49.593 --> 11:51.562
Living in the future.

12:05.643 --> 12:06.877
Do you know one of them?

12:06.910 --> 12:09.513
Is there a way
to make it closer?

12:15.152 --> 12:16.596
You do. You know
one of the boys, don't you?

12:16.620 --> 12:19.022
They're wearing masks.

12:19.056 --> 12:21.224
But you can see their eyes.

12:22.726 --> 12:24.494
That one...

12:25.763 --> 12:27.665
In the middle.

12:27.698 --> 12:29.800
The one who shot the camera.
I know him.

12:29.833 --> 12:31.201
Do you know his name?

12:31.234 --> 12:33.571
Farmer.

12:33.604 --> 12:35.205
Jeffrey Farmer.

12:35.238 --> 12:37.741
Farmer?
Is he your brother?

12:39.209 --> 12:41.779
No, detective, Jeffrey...

12:41.812 --> 12:43.814
Jeffrey's my son.

12:50.921 --> 12:52.623
I moved here from Ojai
when I was 15,

12:52.656 --> 12:54.892
pregnant with Jeffrey.

12:54.925 --> 12:57.160
I found work in a gas station.

12:57.194 --> 12:58.996
I bought that gas station.

12:59.029 --> 13:01.565
I bought another.

13:01.599 --> 13:03.066
Then I bought four more.

13:03.100 --> 13:05.202
Somewhere in there,

13:05.235 --> 13:06.604
Jeffrey grew up.

13:06.637 --> 13:08.806
Somewhere in there,

13:08.839 --> 13:12.943
Jeffrey grew away from me.

13:12.976 --> 13:14.745
It started in high school,

13:14.778 --> 13:17.280
his hatred
of all the immigrants.

13:17.314 --> 13:19.717
Persians.

13:19.750 --> 13:22.753
Do you know the names
of the people he runs with?

13:27.891 --> 13:30.694
They're...
They're surf rats.

13:30.728 --> 13:31.895
He and his two buddies.

13:31.929 --> 13:33.897
Do you know where
we might look for him?

13:33.931 --> 13:36.566
They live out of that van.

13:38.101 --> 13:40.704
I know he did a terrible thing.

13:42.172 --> 13:44.174
But you will bring him back...

13:44.207 --> 13:45.643
Won't you?

13:45.676 --> 13:47.878
[Woman screams]

13:50.914 --> 13:52.282
[Sobbing, speaking in Farsi]

13:52.315 --> 13:54.284
What do you--
what--what--

14:03.126 --> 14:05.763
Trace that. Now.

14:06.964 --> 14:08.098
We're gonna help you, okay?

14:08.131 --> 14:09.232
We're gonna find him.

14:16.173 --> 14:18.676
So he's just gonna buy all this?

14:18.709 --> 14:20.177
If he wants.

14:20.210 --> 14:22.079
'Cause he saw it in a dream.

14:22.112 --> 14:24.147
Apparently.

14:24.181 --> 14:25.949
It's nice that
he still has dreams

14:25.983 --> 14:27.685
after what he came through.

14:27.718 --> 14:29.319
I don't think
I could do what he did,

14:29.352 --> 14:30.754
be that strong.

14:30.788 --> 14:31.755
I don't know.

14:31.789 --> 14:34.725
You seem pretty strong to me.

14:34.758 --> 14:36.727
Everybody turning
their back on you?

14:36.760 --> 14:40.798
Your own loved ones
just... walking away?

14:40.831 --> 14:42.800
It's all we really have
in this world, isn't it?

14:42.833 --> 14:44.902
The ones we love,
the ones who love us.

14:48.839 --> 14:51.008
Energy out of light, huh?

14:52.843 --> 14:55.779
Well, Charlie likes light.

14:55.813 --> 14:57.981
I can imagine.

14:58.015 --> 14:59.783
No, you can't.

15:01.785 --> 15:03.320
No, I can't.
Of course not.

15:03.353 --> 15:06.256
How could I?

15:27.344 --> 15:31.181
[Engine sputtering]

15:34.785 --> 15:37.755
[Giggling]

15:37.788 --> 15:40.357
What is so funny?

15:40.390 --> 15:41.825
It's just that we--

15:41.859 --> 15:45.062
we're surrounded
by all this free energy.

15:45.095 --> 15:47.330
And why is that funny?

15:47.364 --> 15:50.367
Because, Ted, we're out of gas.

15:52.435 --> 15:54.371
[Giggling]

15:57.140 --> 15:58.809
Oh...

16:06.016 --> 16:08.451
It's not funny.

16:14.357 --> 16:15.902
Reese:
Disposable cell phone.
Easy enough to track.

16:15.926 --> 16:18.962
But they'll use a new one
next time they call.

16:28.071 --> 16:29.506
Call coming in on her cell.

16:38.949 --> 16:40.117
Hello?

16:40.150 --> 16:42.152
Man:
We want the cash
from the dope

16:42.185 --> 16:43.821
he and his a-rab friends
are dealing.

16:43.854 --> 16:45.856
You tell us where it is,

16:45.889 --> 16:47.791
or Amir ends up
like his two buddies--

16:47.825 --> 16:49.492
bang, bang.

17:05.008 --> 17:06.243
It's not about

17:06.276 --> 17:07.586
keeping immigrants
out of that neighborhood.

17:07.610 --> 17:09.246
It's about drugs and money.

17:09.279 --> 17:10.480
What have we learned?

17:10.513 --> 17:13.250
[Together, in monotone]
It's always about drugs
and money.

17:13.283 --> 17:16.319
[Roya yelling in Farsi]

17:16.353 --> 17:18.121
Who let this happen?

17:18.155 --> 17:20.290
Who let these two women
near each other?

17:20.323 --> 17:21.558
I'm sorry--
[Yelling]

17:21.591 --> 17:24.127
I just wanted
to come over--

17:24.161 --> 17:27.330
I just wanted to apologize.
I don't know what she's saying.

17:27.364 --> 17:30.133
She wants to know
what kind of a mother

17:30.167 --> 17:32.235
raises a son
who does such things,

17:32.269 --> 17:34.171
what kind of a mother raises

17:34.204 --> 17:36.806
that kind of animal?

17:39.642 --> 17:41.111
Tell her...

17:44.882 --> 17:47.217
Tell her that I would
give my life...

17:47.250 --> 17:49.252
For the life of her son.

17:51.421 --> 17:54.557
Tell her that I know
how much she must love him.

17:56.226 --> 17:58.896
[Speaking Farsi]

18:05.568 --> 18:07.905
Okay.

18:07.938 --> 18:09.739
Drugs and money.
Go search Amir's house.

18:13.610 --> 18:15.078
I think I should go.

18:15.112 --> 18:16.914
Uh, you know, at some point,

18:16.947 --> 18:19.917
we'll probably have to put you
on the phone with your son.

18:19.950 --> 18:23.120
We both know
that would be... a mistake.

18:26.356 --> 18:30.358
You're gonna kill my son,
aren't you?

18:47.945 --> 18:49.879
Didn't know you spoke Farsi.

18:50.680 --> 18:51.982
My mom's Persian.

18:52.015 --> 18:54.117
She'd speak it to me growing up.

18:54.151 --> 18:56.019
What about your father?

18:58.255 --> 19:00.958
He forbid it
when he was in the house.

19:22.545 --> 19:28.351
[Roya speaking Farsi]

19:28.385 --> 19:30.253
[Translating]
My son is not
a drug dealer.

19:30.287 --> 19:31.688
He's a good student.
He studies.

19:31.721 --> 19:33.156
He plays video games.

19:33.190 --> 19:35.125
He doesn't get into trouble.

19:35.158 --> 19:37.594
Tell your mother
that he is in trouble,

19:37.627 --> 19:39.997
and we need her
to be honest with us.

19:40.030 --> 19:42.432
She says he's a good son.

19:42.465 --> 19:44.534
He studies and plays
video games.

19:48.605 --> 19:50.473
Techie:
I'll connect
Amir's computer

19:50.507 --> 19:51.608
to the LAPD server

19:51.641 --> 19:54.644
so that they can access it
over in the conference room.

19:54.677 --> 19:57.347
I've never seen
that screen before.

19:57.380 --> 19:58.648
Techie: The department

19:58.681 --> 20:00.193
doesn't let us
computer geeks have guns,

20:00.217 --> 20:01.684
and they don't let
you detectives

20:01.718 --> 20:04.021
have access to this level
of security.

20:33.350 --> 20:34.317
Hey, Reese.

20:34.351 --> 20:35.118
Hmm?

20:35.152 --> 20:39.256
You, me, and Stark
in the elevator.

20:39.289 --> 20:41.158
You had a weird reaction
when he mentioned

20:41.191 --> 20:43.026
the Bank of L.A. shootout.

20:45.262 --> 20:46.596
Did I?

20:46.629 --> 20:49.499
Which I thought was--
I thought it was weird.

20:49.532 --> 20:51.601
Because you weren't even
on the force back then.

20:51.634 --> 20:54.471
Yeah, I was 12 when it happened.

20:54.504 --> 20:55.605
Family stuff.

21:20.697 --> 21:23.300
You know, I've been
gone a while, but, um...

21:23.333 --> 21:25.034
Are computers
supposed to do this?

21:29.672 --> 21:32.675
Hey, there's a computer
problem in the conference room.

21:32.709 --> 21:34.144
Making funny noises.

21:34.177 --> 21:36.246
There's also
flickering lights involved.

21:44.521 --> 21:46.689
Family stuff...

22:09.912 --> 22:11.714
[Whispering] Jack Reese.

22:11.748 --> 22:13.883
Dani's father.

22:14.416 --> 22:16.252
Some kind of offending
liquid in here.

22:19.989 --> 22:22.158
This is why we don't
drink and type, people.

22:28.097 --> 22:30.066
S.W.A.T. Leader,
Jack Reese.

22:51.220 --> 22:52.341
McAllister: These are clean.

22:52.354 --> 22:54.023
If Amir was hiding
drug money somewhere,

22:54.056 --> 22:55.725
he hasn't recorded it there.

22:55.758 --> 22:58.160
It's just basic
business schoolwork.

22:58.194 --> 23:01.197
I will say this, though.
The kid is smart.

23:01.230 --> 23:03.065
Yep. Straight A's.

23:03.099 --> 23:04.133
Nothing in here either.

23:04.166 --> 23:05.434
It's what you'd expect to find

23:05.467 --> 23:07.236
on a 20-year-old's
computer--

23:07.269 --> 23:09.371
music, some porn.

23:09.405 --> 23:11.240
Not very good porn, though.

23:11.273 --> 23:13.075
Sorry you had to see that.

23:13.109 --> 23:15.111
I'll cope somehow.

23:15.144 --> 23:16.178
Anything else?

23:16.212 --> 23:18.147
You sure this was the only
computer in the house?

23:18.180 --> 23:19.982
Mm-hmm. Why?

23:20.016 --> 23:21.984
Well, there's references
to a file,

23:22.018 --> 23:23.419
but I can't find the file.

23:23.452 --> 23:25.254
What's it called?
Farah.

23:25.287 --> 23:26.689
Farah?

23:26.723 --> 23:29.025
That's a girl's name.

23:29.058 --> 23:30.268
And a number.
"Farah, level ten."

23:30.292 --> 23:31.694
Level ten?

23:31.728 --> 23:34.230
She must be hot.

23:34.263 --> 23:36.265
Farah.

23:36.298 --> 23:39.101
No.
[Sighing]

23:39.135 --> 23:40.336
No Farah.

23:40.369 --> 23:42.271
And what about you, Shahnaz?

23:42.304 --> 23:44.707
Does Amir have any
friends named Farah?

23:44.741 --> 23:46.461
No, he doesn't have
any friends named Farah.

24:08.931 --> 24:11.433
You think there has to be
another computer.

24:11.467 --> 24:13.435
There is a file reference

24:13.469 --> 24:16.105
but no file by that name
on this computer.

24:16.138 --> 24:18.140
He's a good son.
He studies.

24:18.174 --> 24:19.942
He plays his video game.

24:19.976 --> 24:22.745
A game console.
It's like a computer, isn't it?

24:22.779 --> 24:25.014
Not like one.
It is one.

24:25.047 --> 24:26.749
It's just a hard drive
with games on it.

24:36.358 --> 24:38.127
The object of this game

24:38.160 --> 24:39.962
is to save the Princess Farah.

24:39.996 --> 24:42.098
You think you can get
to level ten?

24:42.131 --> 24:45.301
Detective, I'm 30 years old,
I live with my mother, and...

24:45.334 --> 24:49.471
I have a Captain Kirk
costume in my closet.

25:16.298 --> 25:19.268
[Suspenseful music]

25:19.301 --> 25:27.343
♫

27:03.472 --> 27:05.841
Ted, can I ask you a question?

27:05.874 --> 27:07.443
Okay.

27:09.545 --> 27:12.147
You seem like
a nervous sort to me.

27:12.180 --> 27:13.949
Do I?

27:16.552 --> 27:18.520
You were some
Wall Street big shot.

27:18.554 --> 27:20.055
Were you nervous back then?

27:21.923 --> 27:23.459
No.

27:23.492 --> 27:25.160
Did prison make you nervous?

27:25.193 --> 27:29.798
No.

27:29.831 --> 27:31.433
Olivia,

27:31.467 --> 27:33.802
you make me nervous.

27:33.835 --> 27:37.473
That's why I didn't
pay attention to my gas gauge.

27:37.506 --> 27:39.475
That's why we're
stranded out here.

27:39.508 --> 27:42.811
You--you make me nervous.

27:42.844 --> 27:43.945
Oh.

27:47.516 --> 27:48.717
Oh...

27:51.987 --> 27:53.922
That's all right, Ted.

27:53.955 --> 27:57.158
It's human nature.
It's nothing to be ashamed of.

28:07.102 --> 28:10.872
♪ Sweet hour of prayer ♪

28:10.906 --> 28:13.809
♪ Sweet hour of prayer ♪

28:18.146 --> 28:20.516
My dad used to sing it
to me when we camped

28:20.549 --> 28:21.817
when I was a kid.

28:21.850 --> 28:24.452
It's pretty.
Go on.

28:25.821 --> 28:26.788
You sure?

28:26.822 --> 28:28.557
Yeah.

28:31.693 --> 28:36.131
♪ That calls me from ♪

28:36.164 --> 28:39.234
♪ a world of care ♪

28:39.267 --> 28:42.838
♪ And bids me at ♪

28:42.871 --> 28:46.007
♪ my Father's throne ♪

28:46.041 --> 28:50.078
♪ Make all my wants ♪

28:50.111 --> 28:53.181
♪ and wishes known ♪

28:53.214 --> 28:56.752
♪ In seasons of ♪

28:56.785 --> 29:00.155
♪ distress and grief ♪

29:00.188 --> 29:04.292
♪ My soul has often ♪

29:04.325 --> 29:05.927
♪ found release ♪

29:05.961 --> 29:07.929
It's not Amir.

29:07.963 --> 29:10.031
It's not Jeffrey.

29:10.065 --> 29:13.034
Three surf rats
at that gas station.

29:13.068 --> 29:15.203
One of them ends up here dead.

29:15.236 --> 29:18.540
Why do you kill someone
who pulls a job with you?

29:18.574 --> 29:21.309
I guess because you reach
some sort of disagreement.

29:21.342 --> 29:24.079
Mm-hmm. Some sort of
violent disagreement.

29:24.112 --> 29:26.882
And, like Davis says, it's
probably about drugs and money.

29:26.915 --> 29:29.985
Yeah, I guess.
Drugs and money.

29:30.009 --> 29:32.409
♪ Sweet hour of prayer ♪

29:32.821 --> 29:34.289
[Ringing]

29:40.862 --> 29:43.198
[Ringing]

29:48.604 --> 29:49.971
Hello.

29:50.005 --> 29:51.306
Man: Time's up, little sister.

29:51.339 --> 29:52.608
You give me what I want,

29:52.641 --> 29:55.110
or I give your brother
something he does not want.

29:55.143 --> 29:57.045
Got it?

29:57.078 --> 29:59.748
Tell him you found
the information about the money.

29:59.781 --> 30:01.817
Tell him you'll
trade it for your brother.

30:03.351 --> 30:05.020
[Whispering in Farsi]

30:06.655 --> 30:08.657
You can do this, Shahnaz.

30:11.292 --> 30:12.193
Yeah?

30:12.227 --> 30:14.162
Davis:
Jeffrey called in again.

30:14.195 --> 30:17.265
He will exchange Amir for
the information about the money.

30:17.298 --> 30:18.834
You're not gonna do that.

30:18.867 --> 30:20.077
Of course
I'm not going to do that.

30:20.101 --> 30:22.213
I am going to let them think
that we are going to do that.

30:22.237 --> 30:24.305
Rose Bowl parking lot.
45 minutes.

30:24.339 --> 30:25.506
And detectives,

30:25.540 --> 30:28.076
these guys are responsible
for three deaths.

30:28.109 --> 30:30.846
I'd like to end this now.

30:35.350 --> 30:38.019
How long have we been awake?

30:38.053 --> 30:39.721
You sure we are awake?

30:41.189 --> 30:42.357
Maybe this is a dream.

30:42.390 --> 30:44.159
Maybe life is a dream,

30:44.192 --> 30:46.327
and we wake up when we die.

30:46.361 --> 30:48.363
Sun's gonna come up soon, right?

30:48.396 --> 30:51.232
[Exhales]
Something's not right, Reese.

30:51.266 --> 30:53.301
Yeah, tell me about it.

30:59.340 --> 31:02.410
[Ringing]

31:02.443 --> 31:04.345
This is McAllister.

31:04.379 --> 31:05.180
This is Detective Crews.

31:05.213 --> 31:07.182
Talk to me about
those spreadsheets.

31:10.719 --> 31:12.187
Yeah, okay.

31:12.220 --> 31:13.789
Uh...
[Ahem].

31:13.822 --> 31:15.290
According to these spreadsheets,

31:15.323 --> 31:17.301
Amir and his friends
had a nice little drug business.

31:17.325 --> 31:19.260
Three smart USC kids,

31:19.294 --> 31:21.262
a little business school
plus a lot of drugs--

31:21.296 --> 31:22.063
you got an enterprise.

31:22.097 --> 31:24.399
So Jeffrey
and his surf rat friends

31:24.432 --> 31:27.803
bought those drugs
from Amir and company.

31:27.836 --> 31:29.738
Jeffrey figures Amir and company

31:29.771 --> 31:31.740
are sitting on some cash.

31:31.773 --> 31:35.310
They take Amir hostage,
'cause he was their accountant.

31:35.343 --> 31:37.078
He knew where the money was.

31:39.948 --> 31:41.449
Keep looking.
There's more in there.

31:41.482 --> 31:43.284
I don't think there is.

31:43.318 --> 31:45.787
Well, you do something
like this to hide a secret.

31:45.821 --> 31:47.188
More secret
than drugs and money?

31:47.222 --> 31:48.323
Keep lookin'.

31:48.356 --> 31:51.159
It's late, detective.
I've looked.

31:51.192 --> 31:52.293
I have a zen exercise.

31:52.327 --> 31:55.797
It'll give you the energy
you need to finish this task.

31:55.831 --> 31:58.133
Yeah. I really don't
believe in that stuff.

31:58.166 --> 32:00.101
Try it.
Imagine me...

32:00.135 --> 32:02.804
Okay.

32:02.838 --> 32:04.740
Imagine me...

32:04.773 --> 32:07.208
Walking into that room
you are in...

32:07.242 --> 32:10.211
Imagine me walking
into that room you are in...

32:10.245 --> 32:11.379
Okay.

32:11.412 --> 32:12.948
And there you are...

32:12.981 --> 32:15.250
Not having done what I asked.

32:17.418 --> 32:20.288
Okay.

32:20.321 --> 32:21.289
Um...

32:21.322 --> 32:24.192
[Mellow rock music]

32:24.225 --> 32:32.233
♫

32:47.949 --> 32:50.285
Okay. There's--
there's something here.

32:50.318 --> 32:52.520
There's a column here
that doesn't make any sense.

32:52.553 --> 32:54.455
What way doesn't it
make any sense?

32:54.489 --> 32:56.257
It seems to be
a separate business.

32:56.291 --> 33:00.028
Got about $93,000 in cash
in an offshore account.

33:00.061 --> 33:02.397
It's coded with three initials--
M.A.F.

33:05.867 --> 33:07.903
I need an address.

33:07.936 --> 33:10.071
Mary Ann Farmer.

33:10.105 --> 33:11.773
M.A.F.

33:13.108 --> 33:14.309
Turn the car around.

33:15.343 --> 33:17.278
He's not going to that meet.

33:17.312 --> 33:19.214
This is about something else.

33:21.349 --> 33:22.818
He's going
to his mother's house.

33:38.266 --> 33:40.268
This one's not Jeffrey either.

33:45.073 --> 33:47.308
Where's Mary Ann and Amir?

33:47.342 --> 33:48.910
[Whispers] Reese.

33:58.186 --> 34:00.188
He took them in her car.

34:03.958 --> 34:05.593
[Police radio chatter]

34:06.126 --> 34:08.462
So Jeffrey and his surf rat
friends

34:08.495 --> 34:11.165
kill those two
Persian kids and take Amir.

34:11.198 --> 34:13.600
Then Jeffrey
kills his two friends

34:13.633 --> 34:16.070
and takes his mother and Amir.

34:16.103 --> 34:18.906
Jeffrey wants her money too.

34:18.939 --> 34:20.875
He wants more than that.

34:20.908 --> 34:22.142
How do you know?

34:24.111 --> 34:26.280
She told me.

34:26.313 --> 34:28.949
Mary Ann told me.

34:34.054 --> 34:36.056
[Phone ringing]

34:36.090 --> 34:37.091
Crews:
You awake?

34:37.124 --> 34:38.926
Of course.
Sleep is for babies.

34:38.959 --> 34:41.328
Where's the money?

34:41.361 --> 34:43.030
You mean where is it...
Physically?

34:43.063 --> 34:46.233
I guess you could say
it's in the Bahamas.

34:46.266 --> 34:48.002
I wish I was in the Bahamas.

34:48.035 --> 34:49.870
How would Jeffrey get to it?

34:49.904 --> 34:51.071
Wire transfer to any bank.

34:51.105 --> 34:53.407
Is that something we can track?

34:57.111 --> 35:00.014
Just sign here, here, and here,

35:00.047 --> 35:01.247
and I can go get you your cash.

35:01.248 --> 35:02.382
And you, Mr. Darvashi,

35:02.416 --> 35:05.319
you'll be needing
a wire transfer as well?

35:06.954 --> 35:08.989
Yes, please.

35:17.331 --> 35:18.999
[Whispering]
He's gonna kill us.

35:19.033 --> 35:20.167
Shh.

35:21.235 --> 35:23.103
[Whispers] That's right, Amir.

35:23.137 --> 35:24.471
Shh.

35:24.504 --> 35:26.907
He's gonna kill us as soon
as he gets the money.

35:26.941 --> 35:28.909
It's gonna be okay.
No, it won't.

35:28.943 --> 35:30.911
It won't be okay. No.
Yes, it will.

35:30.945 --> 35:33.280
No... More... Talking.

35:33.313 --> 35:35.049
He's gonna kill us.

35:35.082 --> 35:36.592
He's gonna kill us
as soon as we leave the bank.

35:36.616 --> 35:39.253
I saw him kill my friend.
I saw him kill his own friends.

35:39.286 --> 35:40.587
I saw him--aah!

35:40.620 --> 35:43.223
Okay, I might as well
kill you now.

35:43.257 --> 35:46.160
Crews:
Go home?

35:46.193 --> 35:48.963
That's what you wrote on
the glass, isn't it--
Go home.

35:48.996 --> 35:50.998
Is that what you want
them to do,

35:51.031 --> 35:53.000
or is it what you want to do?

35:53.033 --> 35:55.235
Do you want to go home, Jeffrey?

35:55.269 --> 35:56.636
How do you know my name?

35:56.920 --> 35:58.688
I not only know your name,

35:58.722 --> 36:00.524
I also know what you want.

36:00.807 --> 36:03.810
I want this a-rab dead.

36:03.843 --> 36:06.513
He's Persian...
Not arab, Jeffrey.

36:06.546 --> 36:09.516
He's a-rab
if I say he's a-rab!

36:09.549 --> 36:11.585
In about ten seconds,
he's gonna be one dead a-rab.

36:11.618 --> 36:13.453
Crews:
That's not
what you really want.

36:13.487 --> 36:14.664
What you really want
is what Amir has.

36:14.688 --> 36:15.889
You mean, his money.

36:16.990 --> 36:19.192
I'm gonna take his money

36:19.225 --> 36:20.494
and I'll walk outta here

36:20.527 --> 36:23.196
or I'll put his brain
on the floor.

36:23.229 --> 36:25.599
[Amir whimpering]

36:25.632 --> 36:27.033
That's not what
I meant, Jeffrey.

36:27.066 --> 36:30.937
You know what I mean.
You know what Amir has.

36:30.970 --> 36:32.171
Shut up.

36:32.205 --> 36:33.549
See, I thought it was
about the money.

36:33.573 --> 36:35.141
It's always
about the money--

36:35.174 --> 36:37.152
drugs and the money.
Isn't that right, Reese?
That's right.

36:37.176 --> 36:39.746
But your mother
told me the truth.

36:39.779 --> 36:41.147
Whatever she said is a lie.

36:41.180 --> 36:42.882
She's made of lies.

36:43.417 --> 36:46.453
She told Amir's mother...

36:46.486 --> 36:48.688
That she knows how she feels.

36:48.722 --> 36:51.158
She told Amir's mother

36:51.191 --> 36:55.095
that she knows just how much
she must love him.

36:56.263 --> 36:57.297
Jeffrey...

36:57.331 --> 37:00.200
Both of you shut it...
Now!

37:00.234 --> 37:02.002
How could she know that?

37:02.036 --> 37:05.005
How could she know how much
a mother loves her son?

37:05.039 --> 37:06.006
Jeffrey--

37:06.040 --> 37:07.607
I said both of you...

37:07.641 --> 37:09.343
Shut up!

37:09.376 --> 37:11.445
But she doesn't love you.

37:11.478 --> 37:14.248
So she must not have
been talking about you.

37:19.186 --> 37:22.122
Because she loves Amir too.

37:22.156 --> 37:24.158
And that's what you want,
isn't it, Jeffrey?

37:24.191 --> 37:26.293
What Amir has.

37:26.326 --> 37:28.262
What your mother's giving him.

37:31.598 --> 37:33.133
It's love.

37:34.734 --> 37:36.503
Right?

37:40.474 --> 37:42.509
[Man over headset]
S.W.A.T. Two.
I'm in position.

37:42.542 --> 37:44.311
And something else too.

37:46.346 --> 37:47.381
[Gunshot]

37:47.414 --> 37:48.482
[Gasps]

38:03.763 --> 38:04.764
Mom?

38:19.513 --> 38:22.482
[Fiddle music]

38:22.516 --> 38:30.524
♫

38:38.798 --> 38:40.600
Good morning.

39:08.628 --> 39:10.264
Amir would come into my store

39:10.297 --> 39:12.266
when he was still
in high school.

39:13.367 --> 39:16.136
I have a lot of soft
cash in my business,

39:16.170 --> 39:18.214
and he showed me there were
better things to do with it

39:18.238 --> 39:19.906
than keep it in a bag
in my closet.

39:19.939 --> 39:21.775
And you fell in love.

39:24.344 --> 39:27.647
He wasn't like
the rest of the kids.

39:27.681 --> 39:30.384
Wasn't like
Jeffrey and his friends.

39:30.417 --> 39:33.620
Amir wanted to be something.

39:36.290 --> 39:37.791
He worked at it.

39:37.824 --> 39:40.260
The kind of kid who could
start out pumping gas

39:40.294 --> 39:42.462
and end up owning
six gas stations?

39:56.710 --> 40:00.314
Yeah, I think maybe
one more just to get me home.

40:04.418 --> 40:06.486
Thanks.

40:18.465 --> 40:19.799
Going out?

40:19.833 --> 40:21.968
Ted:
Yeah, yeah.

40:22.001 --> 40:24.871
I got some...
stuff to do.

40:30.410 --> 40:32.379
